  "titleRaw": "Versioning of Content Assets",
  "excerptRaw": "",
  "bodyHtml": "Everyone makes mistakes, big and small. There is no easy way to return within the Content Management system built into Salesforce B2C Commerce Cloud&nbsp;once you save a Content Asset.\n\nIt is easy as pie to roll back changes to even months ago within many plugins and editors (including <a href=\"http://elementor.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Elementor</a>, which I use for this blog.)\n\nThis is most certainly a missing feature in Page Designer and Content Assets!\n\n<style>/*! elementor - v3.6.1 - 23-03-2022 */<br />\n.elementor-widget-image{text-align:center}.elementor-widget-image a{display:inline-block}.elementor-widget-image a img[src$=\".svg\"]{width:48px}.elementor-widget-image img{vertical-align:middle;display:inline-block}</style>\n<figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img width=\"800\" height=\"419\" src=\"https://www.rhino-inquisitor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/revision-blog-1024x536.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://www.rhino-inquisitor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/revision-blog-1024x536.jpg 1024w, https://www.rhino-inquisitor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/revision-blog-300x157.jpg 300w, https://www.rhino-inquisitor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/revision-blog-768x402.jpg 768w, https://www.rhino-inquisitor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/revision-blog.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><figcaption>Revisions in Elementor</figcaption></figure>\n<a href=\"https://ideas.salesforce.com/s/idea/a0B8W00000GdVsJUAV/versioning-of-content-assets\" role=\"button\">\nVote for this idea here\n</a>",
